Starry sky has an appointmentä¸¨The Geminid meteor shower will be extremely large on Dec. 14 - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency, Tianjin, Dec. 12 (Xinhua) -- As the last large-scale meteor shower of the year, the Geminid meteor shower, one of the three major meteor showers in the northern hemisphere, will be extremely large on Dec. 14, and friends who like meteor showers can observe it in the latter half of the day. Beijing astronomy enthusiast Anjiu photographed the Geminid meteor shower in Qinghai on Dec. 13, 2018. The parent object of most meteor showers is a periodic comet, but the parent object of the Geminid meteor shower is the asteroid 3200 Fahrenheit, which is an Apollo-type asteroid. The Geminid meteor shower is also the second known meteor shower that was not "birthed" by a comet. Tianjin Astronomical Society director, astronomy science expert Xiu Lipeng said, like the New Year's blockbuster, Geminid meteor shower generally appear at the end of the year, "the release schedule" can last from December 4 to 17. The meteor shower is known for its high and steady flow, and is known as one of the top three meteor showers in the northern hemisphere, along with the Quadrantid meteor shower and the Perseid meteor shower. A distinctive feature of the Geminid meteor shower is the slow speed of meteoroids, rich colors and many fire meteors, which are suitable for both visual and beginner astrophotographers to shoot. Tianjin astronomy enthusiast Yang Jingjing photographed the Geminid meteor shower in Jizhou, Tianjin on Dec. 13, 2020. The astronomical forecast shows that this year's Geminid meteor shower will be extremely large at around 15:00 on December 14, with a ZHR (the number of meteors visible per hour when the radiation point is located directly above the head under ideal observation conditions) of 150. Geminid meteor shower recommended index chart. "Last year, the Geminid meteor shower left a deep impression on people, but this year's Geminid meteor shower will be interfered by the moonlight, and the wonderful degree will be a little discounted. 14 is the eleventh month of the lunar calendar, the moon phase is surplus convex moon, the bright moonlight will interfere with the observation, but the good thing is that the moon will set in the second half of the night, and the radiation point will rise higher at this time. The moon will set in the second half of the night, and the radiant point of the Geminid meteor shower will rise higher at this time. If you like meteor showers, you can observe them in the second half of the night, after the moon has set, but be careful to keep warm. "How can we observe as many meteors as possible? "It is not recommended to observe in the city, but in the suburbs or the countryside, choose a place with a high altitude, little light damage, and an open view facing northeast, then patiently wait until the moon sets and observe visually. It should be noted that the Geminid meteor shower has a large flow in all directions, so you do not need to keep staring at the radiation point of the Geminid meteor shower when observing. For those who like photography, it is best to choose a wide-angle lens with a large aperture and use a high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting to produce a gorgeous 'meteor shower. Based on stability and sustainability considerations, tripods, spare batteries and shutter cables are also essential . "Xiu Lipeng reminded.
